    "Other tasks or datasets may require using different resolution selection strategies.",
    "To confirm that our data augmentation strategy (Fig. 1B) mitigated the technical biases from slide to slide or institution to institution due to staining, scanning and other factors, we tested whether the identified clusters are patient-specific or institution-specific.",
    "The number of patients who contribute tiles in each cluster is shown in Fig. 2B, demonstrating that none of the identified clusters is patientspecific, and all clusters but the last one (HPC 45) receive contributing tiles from at least 17%(78/452) patients.",
    "Overall, the HPCs are highly recurrent, appearing in a median of 32%(133/452) of all patients.",
    "Similarly, Fig. 2C shows the number of institutions that contribute to each cluster: no cluster was found to be institution specific, and all clusters but the last one contain tiles from at least 24%(8/33) institutions."
